#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:5
msgid "Emscripten Toolchain Requirements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:7
msgid ""
"The instructions below list the main tools and dependencies in an Emscripten "
"environment, along with instructions on how to test which dependencies are "
"installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:9
msgid ""
"The :ref:`SDK <sdk-download-and-install>` provides the **easiest** and "
"**most reliable** method for getting, using, updating and managing "
"Emscripten environments. If you're using the SDK you won't *need* these "
"instructions — they are provided for information only."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:11
msgid ""
"The instructions below are useful if you're :ref:`manually <installing-from-"
"source>` building from source."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:16
msgid "What you'll need"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:21
msgid "Emscripten tools and dependencies"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:23
msgid ""
"In general a complete Emscripten environment requires the following tools. "
"First test to see if they are already installed using the :ref:`instructions "
"below <toolchain-test-which-dependencies-are-installed>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:25
msgid ":term:`Node.js` (18.3.0 or above)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:26
msgid ":term:`Python` (3.8 or above)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:27
msgid ""
":term:`Java` (1.6.0_31 or later). Java is optional. It can be used to run "
"the java version of term:`Closure Compiler`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:28
msgid ":term:`Git` client. Git is required if building tools from source."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:29
msgid ":term:`LLVM` (LLVM, including clang and wasm-ld)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:30
msgid ""
":term:`Binaryen` (Binaryen, including wasm-opt, wasm-emscripten-finalize, "
"etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:31
msgid ""
"The `Emscripten code <https://github.com/emscripten-core/emscripten>`_, from "
"GitHub"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/building_from_source/toolchain_what_is_needed.rst:35
msgid ""
"The `d8 shell <https://v8.dev/docs/d8>`_ is also required if you want to run "
"**100%** of the tests in the test suite (in particular, tests for extremely "
"new features that are only present in d8 so far). Most developers will not "
"need this, and should instead use *node.js*."
msgstr ""

